title: Apple#039;s iPhone 6s Breaks Record, as China Boosts Sales to 13 Million
text:
Get Business & Technology Alerts 
29 Sep 2015 05:27 AM EST 
According to The Guardian, enthusiasm in China drove sales of Apple’s latest iPhone to a record 13 million units last weekend, topping last year’s record of 10 million. Analysts put sales in China at between 3 million and 4 million units, leaving sales elsewhere essentially flat year-over-year. The phone’s major upgrades include what Apple is calling 3D touch, in which the touchscreen responds not solely to touch but to pressure, as well, and the standard camera megapixel and processor improvements.
